4Geeks Academy offers a Cybersecurity Bootcamp that allows individuals to become cybersecurity specialists, even with no prior knowledge in the field. The bootcamp aims to equip students with a solid foundation in Windows, Linux, network, and server administration, as well as practical skills in securing these environments. Additionally, students will learn about cloud security, penetration testing, cyber threat intelligence analysis, data loss prevention strategies, and compliance with international standards such as ISO 27001 and NIST. The program lasts for 16 weeks, with three live online classes per week. The class size is limited to 16 people. Upon completion, students will receive an official 4Geeks Completion Certificate recognized by multiple institutions. No previous experience is required to enroll in the bootcamp. The median annual salary for cybersecurity professionals in the United States is $103,560. For more information, visit https://4geeksacademy.com/us/coding-bootcamps/cybersecurity.